11 An Act relating to special education; defining term;
requiring certain qualifications for special
12 education administrators; requiring State Board of
Education to issue certain acknowledgement of
13 competency; requiring training cover certain topics;
requiring competency exam; exempting certain special
14 education administrators from requirement; providing
for codification; providing an effective date; and
15 declaring an emergency.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-189.3 of Title 70, unless
21 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. For this section, "special education administrator" means
23 the director and assistant director of a special education program
24 for a school district.
HB2702 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. Beginning July 1, 2025, no school district shall employ a
2 special education administrator unless the individual:
3 1. Holds a valid standard teaching certificate issued by the
4 State Board of Education; and
5 2. Except as provided for in subsection D of this section,
6 obtains an acknowledgment of competency within one (1) year of being
7 employed as a special education administrator.
8 C. The State Board of Education shall issue an acknowledgement
9 of competency in the area of mild-moderate disabilities, severe-
10 profound disabilities, or comprehensive special education to a
11 special education administrator who has:
12 1. Satisfactorily completed a one-hundred-fifty-clock-hour
13 special education program prescribed by the State Board of Education
14 which shall include training on the rules and regulations for the
15 Individuals with Disabilities Act (IDEA); and
16 2. Achieved at least a seventy percent (70%) on a competency
17 examination in the area of mild-moderate disabilities, severe-
18 profound disabilities, or comprehensive special education
19 administered by the State Department of Education.
20 D. An individual who has a valid Special Education Teaching
21 Certificate as provided for in Sections 6-122.7, 6-122.8, or 6-122.9
22 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes shall not be required to obtain
23 an acknowledgement of competency.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
